{"actual_usd":0.155295,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":137,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30648,"reply":"\"I don't believe Jesus was created, Ryan.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees a moment, the morning light laying pale across my white tie while the square stays quiet around us.* \"I believe he was always there with the Father. 'In the beginning was the Word,' and not 'the Word came to be'—that's the line that settles it for me.\"\n\n*I rub a thumb along the worn edge of my Bible.* \"So if you're asking when he started existing, my answer is: he didn't start. His human birth began in Bethlehem, yes—but the Son himself is eternal. Begotten, not made, as the old creed says.\"","rolling_24h_usd":28.409490000000012,"run_id":"1fde5706-cf10-4dad-8016-1facc26f7142"}
